.TH CHATTOR 1 "February 2026" "chattor 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chattor \- peer\-to\-peer encrypted chat over Tor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chattor
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B chattor
is a terminal chat application where each user runs their own Tor hidden
service via the embedded arti library. Messages are end\-to\-end encrypted with
Signal Protocol (X3DH key exchange + ChaCha20\-Poly1305). There are no central
servers, no accounts, and no metadata leakage. Each peer is both a client and
a server.
.PP
Your identity is an Ed25519 keypair generated on first launch. Your v3 .onion
address is created and managed by arti, persisting across restarts. No system
Tor installation is required \(em arti bootstraps and maintains Tor circuits
internally. Connection pooling reuses Tor circuits per peer for faster
messaging.
.PP
All data is stored locally in a SQLCipher\-encrypted database. Messages are
searchable via FTS5 full\-text search. Nothing is stored on remote servers or
third\-party infrastructure.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable debug logging. Output goes to stderr.
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-theme\fR \fINAME\fR
Set the color theme. Available presets:
.BR dark " (default),"
.BR light ,
.BR cyberpunk ,
.BR minimal ,
.BR rose\-pine ,
.BR rose\-pine\-moon ,
.BR rose\-pine\-dawn .
See
.B THEMES
section.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR
Use a custom configuration and data directory instead of the platform default.
Useful for running multiple isolated instances.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help information and exit. Use \fB\-\-help\fR for extended help with
keybindings.
.SH GETTING STARTED
.TP
.B 1.
Build and run:
.B cargo build \-\-release && cargo run
.TP
.B 2.
On first launch, an Ed25519 identity is generated and arti begins bootstrapping
to the Tor network. An animated screen shows progress (typically 10\-30 seconds).
.TP
.B 3.
Once connected, the main TUI loads. Press
.B i
to view your identity \(em your .onion address and friend code.
.TP
.B 4.
Share your friend code or .onion address with someone. They press
.B a
and paste it to send you a friend request.
.TP
.B 5.
When a friend request arrives, press
.B f
to view requests, select one, then
.B A
to accept or
.B R
to reject.
.TP
.B 6.
Select a friend with Tab/arrows and press Enter. Type a message and press
Enter to send.
