.SH FRIEND CODES
Friend codes are 32\-word mnemonics derived from your Ed25519 public key. Each
byte of the 32\-byte key maps to one word from a fixed 256\-word dictionary,
making the encoding deterministic and reversible.
.PP
Codes are displayed as 8 groups of 4 words. Words within a group are separated
by dashes; groups are separated by spaces. Example:
.PP
.RS
ace\-act\-add\-age ago\-aid\-aim\-air ale\-all\-and\-ant ...
.RE
.PP
When adding a friend, you can paste either a friend code or a raw .onion
address \(em both are accepted.
.SH BROADCAST CHANNELS
Each user automatically has two broadcast channels: Public and Friends Only.
Public channels are visible to anyone who knows your .onion address. Friends
Only channels are limited to accepted friends.
.PP
Posts are Ed25519\-signed by the publisher, ensuring authenticity. Subscribers
pull new posts periodically (every 5 minutes) via sync requests. Publishers see
a "seen by N" read receipt count per post.
.PP
Channels retain the 100 most recent posts. When friends accept each other, they
automatically subscribe to each other's channels.
.SH THEMES
.B chattor
ships with 7 color themes. Set via
.B \-\-theme
flag or in the TOML config file.
.TP
.B dark
Muted grays with blue accents. Default theme.
.TP
.B light
Bright background with dark text.
.TP
.B cyberpunk
Neon greens and magentas on a dark background.
.TP
.B minimal
Monochrome, low contrast.
.TP
.B rose\-pine
Soft pink and gold tones on a dark background.
.TP
.B rose\-pine\-moon
Rose Pine variant with cooler tones.
.TP
.B rose\-pine\-dawn
Light variant of Rose Pine.
.PP
Custom colors can be set in
.I ~/.config/chattor/theme.toml
(Linux) or
.I ~/Library/Application\\ Support/chattor/theme.toml
(macOS). Any color field from the built\-in themes can be overridden using hex
color values.
.SH SHELL COMPLETIONS
Shell completion scripts are included in the
.B completions/
directory of the source distribution.
.TP
.B Bash
Copy
.I completions/chattor.bash
to
.IR ~/.local/share/bash\-completion/completions/chattor .
.TP
.B Zsh
Copy
.I completions/_chattor
to a directory in your
.BR $fpath .
.TP
.B Fish
Copy
.I completions/chattor.fish
to
.IR ~/.config/fish/completions/ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/chattor/theme.toml
Theme color overrides (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/chattor/messages.db
SQLCipher\-encrypted database containing messages, friends, channels, and
identity (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application\\ Support/chattor/
Configuration and data directory (macOS). Contains both theme config and
database.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B chattor
Start with default settings and dark theme.
.TP
.B chattor \-\-theme cyberpunk
Start with the cyberpunk color theme.
.TP
.B chattor \-\-config\-dir /tmp/alice
Run an isolated instance with a separate database. Useful for testing with two
users side by side.
.TP
.B chattor \-\-debug 2>chattor.log
Run with debug logging redirected to a file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tor (1),
